# Normalize all text files to LF in the repository and on checkout, on every
# platform. This ends the "LF will be replaced by CRLF" churn that Git for
# Windows' autocrlf otherwise produces, and keeps diffs identical for Windows
# and Linux contributors. PowerShell and Inno Setup both run LF-terminated
# files fine, so no per-script CRLF override is needed.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Treat known binary assets as binary: never line-ending-normalize or try to
# diff them as text.
*.ico   binary
*.png   binary
*.jpg   binary
*.jpeg  binary
*.gif   binary
*.zip   binary
*.gdraw binary
*.exe   binary
*.dll   binary

# Mark generated/vendored content so GitHub's language stats and diffs behave.
docs/BUILDPLAN-v0.9-archive.md linguist-documentation
